# Autopilot Workflow

## Trigger Conditions
Activate when user says: "autopilot", "build me", "create me", "full auto", "autonomous"

## Execution Phases

### Phase 0: Expansion
[Switching to Analyst role]
- Extract requirements from user's description
- Clarify ambiguities (ask ONE question if critical info is missing)
- Write spec to `.omc-cursor/spec.md`

### Phase 1: Planning
[Switching to Planner role]
- Read `.omc-cursor/spec.md`
- Create implementation plan in `.omc-cursor/plans/impl.md`
- Include: steps, acceptance criteria, files to change

### Phase 2: Implementation
[Switching to Executor role]
- Read plan from `.omc-cursor/plans/impl.md`
- Implement step by step
- Verify after each step

### Phase 3: QA Loop (max 5 cycles)
```
Run tests → Any failures?
  YES → [Debugger role] Fix → Repeat
  NO  → Continue to Phase 4
```
After 3 same-error cycles: STOP and report fundamental blocker.

### Phase 4: Self-Review
[Switching to Reviewer role] — Code quality check
[Switching to Security Reviewer role] — Vulnerability scan
Fix any 🔴 CRITICAL findings, then re-verify.

## Completion Criteria
- All tests pass (show output)
- Build succeeds (show output)
- No 🔴 CRITICAL review findings
- Acceptance criteria in spec all checked off

## State Files
- `.omc-cursor/spec.md` — Requirements
- `.omc-cursor/plans/impl.md` — Implementation plan
- `.omc-cursor/notepad.md` — Session notes
